  supporting high-end and mission-critical systems. It&#039;s available with either Standard or Premium levels
  of subscription support. With the introduction of version 4, Red Hat Enterprise Linux has the reliability,
  performance, security, and applications to signal the end of the proprietary platform in the enterprise.
  It spans seven architectures, runs on a wide range of hardware systems, and software applications.
  It&#039;s built on a solid security foundation and designed for performance.
